Subject: Follow-Up: User Authentication Issue on New Platform

Hi [Recipient Name],

I’m following up regarding the user authentication issue on the new platform. To help with troubleshooting, I’ve included the relevant error logs and code snippets below.

Error Logs:
```text
[2026-04-23 10:14:32] ERROR: Authentication failed for user_id=4821
Reason: Invalid token signature
Endpoint: /api/v2/auth/login
Trace ID: 9f3a2c7d1b

[2026-04-23 10:15:07] ERROR: OAuth callback processing failed
Reason: Redirect URI mismatch
Provider: ExampleAuth
Trace ID: 3ab8e19f4c
```

Code Snippet:
```javascript
async function authenticateUser(token) {
  try {
    const response = await authClient.verifyToken({
      token: token,
      redirectUri: process.env.AUTH_REDIRECT_URI
    });
    return response.user;
  } catch (error) {
    console.error('Authentication error:', error.message);
    throw error;
  }
}
```

Based on the logs, the issue may be related to an invalid token signature or a redirect URI mismatch in the authentication configuration. Please review the token validation settings and confirm that the configured redirect URI matches the one registered with the authentication provider.

If you need any additional details or would like me to send more logs, I’d be happy to help.

Best regards,
[Your Name]

